Astoria Boulevard, at the southwest corner of79th Street, showing the A. R. Luyster farmhouse, a pre-Revolutionary building. rebuilt. L. Douglas owned it in 1873. In 1907 it was known as Gus. Busehatzki's Terminal Hotel and in 1922 as Busehatzki's Hotel.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  May, 1923
